SIMPLE: unthread
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unthread
<hw>Un*thread"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>thread</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To draw or take out a thread from; <as>as, to
<ex>unthread</ex> a needle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of ligaments; to loose the ligaments
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He with his bare wand can <qex>unthread</qex> thy joints.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To make one's way through; to traverse; <as>as, to
<ex>unthread</ex> a devious path</as>.</def> <rj><au>De
Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unthrift</ent>⟦br⟧
